    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-02T11:21:52+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-02T11:21:52+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-02T01:51:52Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T01:51:52Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A series of low pressure systems passing over waters to the south will extend cold fronts that will cross over SA through to the end of the week. A high pressure system is then forecast to move into the Bight from late Friday and extend a ridge across the state over the weekend, as it slowly moves southeastwards towards Tasmania.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW002" description="Yorke Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers, becoming less likely in the evening. Winds westerly 30 to 45 km/h. Daytime maximum temperatures around 15.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower, most likely in the early morning. Winds westerly 30 to 45 km/h turning southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h early in the morning then decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog. Slight chance of a shower. Light winds becoming southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 6 with daytime temperatures reaching around 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the south, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds easterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching around 14.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
